  <description>This extension allows GameMaker:Studio HTML5 projects to connect to the Kongregate API. If you test locally using these functions, the extension automatically ignores JavaScript errors you normally would have because local testing doesn't load the Kongregate API. To get your game on Kongregate you need to download the Kongregate shell html file (kongregate_shell.html) and change the embedFrame() method to "index.html" or whatever name matches your game's main html file. Upload your game to a webhost, along with the kongregate_shell.html file. Submit your IFRAME game with the proper settings. The url should be "http://yourwebsitehere.com/.../kongregate_shell.html". Click upload and you should now see your game in the Kongregate preview window. Your API calls and functions should now work online, on Kongregate's website alone.</description>
